{
  "texts": [
    "In real-world applications, series of D are often unequal length.",
    "This is often treated as a preprocessing task, i.e.",
    "by appending tailing zeros, although some algorithms have the capability to internally handle this.",
    "We further typically assume that all time series of D have the same sampling frequency, i.e., every i th data point of every series was measured at the same temporal distance from its predecessor.",
    "The bake off conducted experiments with the 85 UTSC datasets that were in the UCR archive relaunch of 2015."
  ]
}